My recommendation — a small class hierarchy where each error also carries a **literal `code`**, so you get both `instanceof` *and* exhaustive `switch (err.code)` (which plays well with the repo's exhaustive-switch rule):

```ts
class ConcurrencyError extends Error { readonly code: string }

class CancelledError              extends ConcurrencyError { code = "cancelled" }
class TimeoutError                extends ConcurrencyError { code = "timeout" }
class CoroutineAlreadyStartedError extends ConcurrencyError { code = "already_started" }
class ChannelClosedError          extends ConcurrencyError { code = "channel_closed" }
class WaitGroupError              extends ConcurrencyError { code = "waitgroup" }
